A 10-year-old Celtic superfan (with Down's Syndrome) has been nominated for the SPFL  Goal of the Month for January after being invited to take part in a half-time penalty shootout challenge.

Jay Beatty of Armagh captured the hearts of a nation when he was plucked from the crowd by former Hoops striker Georgios Samaras to join in last year's title winning celebrations.

A video of him enjoying Celtic's lap of honour was shown live on Sky Sports and gathered over two million hits on YouTube after going viral.

