Samaras, who has since left the club and currently plays for Saudi side Al Hilal  on loan, was so taken with Beatty that he invited him to last year's World Cup in Brazil.

'This boy gives me so much strength, it's incredible,' Samaras said last year. 'There are no words. I feel his love so much. This love I feel, is also felt by many people in Greece.' 

Beatty's goal, which is reportedly leading the votes, will compete for the SPFL Goal of the Month alongside the likes of David Goodwillie, Gary Macakay-Steven, and Mikael Lustig.

